  "niche": {
    "entity_count": 120,
    "description": "Curated EUKARYOTE contaminant-anchor roster x spliced CDS GCF_000002855.3 ASM285v2 (NCBI, public domain). 11 representative loci (NOT genome-complete \u2014 a 33.9 Mb / ~14k-gene mold): the conidiation / airborne-spore cascade (fluG, stuA, brlA->abaA->wetA, the dewA spore-wall hydrophobin) + the conidial melanin pigment oxidase (the 'black mold' identity) + the saprotroph metabolism backbone (glaA glucoamylase = external starch digestion, the citA citrate synthase of the citric-acid factory that acidifies out competitors, gpdA, niaD nitrate assimilation). A. niger CBS 513.88: 33.9 Mb / 8 chr / ~14,165 ORFs; prolific airborne conidia (you inhale hundreds daily), hyphae outgrow + acidify out bacteria -> takes the plate ('lab weeds'). The immigration kernel reads role + trait levers, not specific genes (ADR-019 S0).",
